<ul>
    <li><strong>The Breaking Point:</strong> Running from crisis to crisis, eating lunch in my car, bringing work home every night—and still feeling like I was failing everyone.</li>
    <li><strong>The Hard Truth:</strong> I was the single point of failure in a broken system. When I wasn't available, everything fell apart.</li>
    <li><strong>The Realization:</strong> Working harder wasn't the answer—I was already at maximum capacity. Something fundamental had to change.</li>
</ul>
